<DOC><DOCNO> AP880715-0124 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-07-15-88 1227EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Yugoslavia-Heat     07-15 0067</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Yugoslavia-Heat,0069</SECOND><HEAD>48 Die Of Heat In Belgrade</HEAD><DATELINE>BELGRADE, Yugoslavia (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Record heat in Yugoslavia caused thedeath of 48 people in Belgrade this week, a newspaper said Friday.   Most of the victims were heart patients who suffered heatstroke, the Vecernje Novosti newspaper said in a report quotingdoctors.   Since the beginning of July, temperatures of 100 and higher havebeen recorded throughout Yugoslavia.</TEXT></DOC>